  "prompt": "How does flitto app make money?",
  "response": "Flitto is a crowdsourced translation platform that generates revenue through several methods:\n\n1. Translation Services\n- Charging users for professional translations\n- Offering paid translation services to individuals and businesses\n\n2. Crowdsourcing Model\n- Users can earn money by translating content for others\n- Flitto takes a percentage of the transaction fees\n\n3. Language Exchange\n- Connecting language learners for mutual translation and learning\n- Potentially charging for premium features or subscriptions\n\n4. Corporate Translation Solutions\n- Providing translation services for businesses\n- Offering enterprise-level translation platforms\n\n5. Digital Content Translation\n- Translating digital content like websites, apps, and marketing materials\n- Charging for specialized translation services\n\n6. Advertising and Partnerships\n- Potential revenue from in-app advertising\n- Collaborations with language learning platforms or educational institutions\n\nThe core of Flitto's business model is leveraging a community of bilingual users to provide quick, affordable translation services while generating revenue through various channels.",
